         <abstract>
            <p>We derive a lower error bound for monotone difference schemes to the solution of the linear advection equation with BV initial data. A rigorous analysis shows that for any monotone difference scheme the lower L&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt;-error bound is &lt;tex-math&gt;$O(\sqrt{\Delta x})$&lt;/tex-math&gt;, where Δ x is the spatial stepsize.</p>
          </abstract>
